Scripting

idea > code > deployment > running reliably

steps:
.plan the script 
    .define the purpose/ problem to solve  
    .inputs - files, user input, API calls 
    .outputs - print to console, write to file, send data to API 
    .dependencies - libraries, tools, services
    .runtime environment 
.set up the environment 
    .install necessary tools and libraries
    .create project folder and files
    .create virtual environment 
        > then activate it 
.write the script 
    .use functions 
    .add comments and documentation
.install dependencies 
    .install and freeze them  
.test the script 
    .maual testing
        .automated testing for larger projects/ pro levels 
.refactor and organize 
    .split code into modules 
    .add error handling and logging
    .add configuration files 
    .replace hardcoded values with variables
.prepare for deployment 
    .run manually to ensure it works as expected
    .turn it into command line tool or web app if needed 
    .package it for distribution 
        .using tools like pyinstaller, setuptools, or Docker
.deploy the script
    .locally 
    .server or cloud platform
        .copy project files 
        .install dependencies
        .set up environment variables 
        .configure permissions and access
.automate the execution 
    .use task schedulers like cron or Windows Task Scheduler 
.monitor and maintain the script 
    .check logs and outputs regularly
    .update dependencies and libraries
    .fix bugs  
    .add new features as needed
    .handle new edge cases 
